<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-29T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2904: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-29T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                            1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 2:49
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>1463. Reference your telegram to London which was repeated to me
                                giving text of proposed joint announcement on August 1st by the four
                                powers concerning the establishment of consortium.<note n="70" xml:id="d547fn70">See footnote 66, <ref target="#pg_558">p.
                                        558</ref>.</note> Foreign Office will make similar
                                announcement on August 1st.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>